Serbia May Turn Part of JAT Into Charter Carrier, Tanjug Reports

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-04-26T07:34:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/serbia-may-turn-part-of-jat-into-charter-carrier-tanjug-reports.html
JAT Airways  may be split up to
include a small charter airline, leaving the bulk of the company
to be offered in a tender this summer,  Tanjug  newswire reported,
citing q government official.  The government plan include “primarily counting on  Turkish
Airlines ” as a buyer, while the remainder, after paying back
company debts, “might carry on as a charter carrier,” the
newswire quoted Deputy Infrastructure Minister Miodrag Miljkovic
as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  